📌 Project Introduction

This project is a data migration and synchronization pipeline built using Python that transfers data from Snowflake (source) to Azure SQL Managed Instance (target).

It is designed to perform incremental data loading, meaning it only processes new or updated records instead of reloading the entire dataset every time.

⚙️ Key Features
Automatic Table Creation
If a table does not exist in Azure SQL, the system automatically creates it based on Snowflake schema.
Schema Comparison & Handling
Detects schema changes and recreates target tables when needed.
Multiple Load Strategies
Supports different data loading methods like:
INSERT only
UPSERT (update + insert)
DELETE + INSERT
TRUNCATE + INSERT
UPSERT with DELETE handling
Staging Table Approach
Uses temporary staging tables to safely process and merge data.
Watermark-Based Incremental Load
Tracks the last updated timestamp to fetch only new/modified records.
Audit Logging System
Logs every operation (start, success, failure, row counts, duration) into audit tables.
Parallel Processing
Uses multithreading to process multiple tables simultaneously for better performance.
🎯 Purpose

The main goal of this project is to build a robust, scalable ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) pipeline that ensures:

Data consistency between Snowflake and Azure SQL
Efficient data transfer
Proper monitoring and error handling